** Entry Wage: this is the wage an entry-level worker might expect 
to make. It is defined as the average (mean) wage earned by the 
lowest third of all workers in a given occupation.

*** Experienced Wage: this wage represents what an experienced 
worker might expect to make. It is defined as the average (mean) 
wage earned by the upper two-thirds of all workers in a given 
occupation.

Florida Department of Commerce, Bureau of Workforce 
Statistics and Economic Research

^Percentile wages are a generalized form of median wage.  It is an 
estimate of what the nth percentile of the population makes working in the 
indicated occupation, industry, and area.
10th percentile - 10 percent of the population make less than this wage and 90 percent make more.
25th percentile – 25 percent of the population make less than this wage and 75 percent make more.
75th percentile – 75 percent of the population make less than this wage and 25 percent make more.
90th percentile – 90 percent of the population make less than this wage and 10 percent make more.
